<br>
&quot;You are hearby ordered to close down this establishment of sin.&quot;  Paladin looked around the room with the air of the self rightous.  The patrons glared back.  Paladin checked to make sure his troops were still there.<br>
<br>
Tantrika spoke several words in dark speak.  A table of trolls blushed.  <br>
<br>
Paladin knew just enough of the language to know she requested certain parts of his body to be stuffed into other parts most unpleasent. And something about his mother and a pack of gnomes.  His body stiffened in rage.<br>
<br>
&quot;heathen harlot!&quot; he spat.  &quot;still thy tounge before I have it chopped loose.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rodlac stepped out from behind the bar.  He carried a sturdy stone tankard.  His steps steady and heavy against the wood floor.  <br>
<br>
Paladin sneered.  &quot;And just who do you think you are now,boy?&quot;  He stepped forward, sword clanking against steel shod boots.  Brown locks fell over brown eyes, head down slightly, peering under sharp brows.<br>
<br>
Rodlac whistled, sharp and single.  A troll stepped from shadows toward Paladin.  Half a goat carcass swung from his left club of a hand.  A slab of haunch hung pierced upon one jagged tooth jutting out from his lower lip.  His other hand carried what may have been a life threatening pike, or a simple toothpick.  Either case, it was longer than Paladin's leg. The troll grabbed him and held him to the ceiling by a swiftly crunching arm.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm the guy who decides if you keep your heart inside your body,&quot; Rodlac grinned.  <br>
<br>
&quot;What are you waiting for?  Charge!&quot; Pal screamed to his troops.  He did not enjoy the noticable delay as they contemplated just how loyal they were.  <br>
<br>
The troll looked to the doorway.  Fire leaped from the frame, forming a wall of flame, yet did not consume the wood.  The heat forced the troops back.  The troll looked back to Pal and spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sir, I'm afraid I must ask you to leave here at once or we will be forced to prostitute.&quot;  Pal's eyelashed curled from the rank breath.  <br>
<br>
&quot;That's uh, prosicute.&quot;  Radlac said.  &quot;But the rest was good.&quot;<br>
<br>
The troll smiled.  Pal snorted.  &quot;as if you know what the word means, brute.&quot;<br>
<br>
The knuckles and shoulders of the Troll popped ominously.  &quot;How dis?  Me show you what me think, you tell me after.&quot;  <br>
<br>
Pal gasped as the hand upon his already crunching arm bone bore down with more force.<br>
