<br>
Rodlac awoke from a dream.  Vague memories excaped his mind as alertness pressed oppressively forward.  He tried to draw back the memory, but all he could think of was drake hide leggings.  Curious.  <br>
<br>
Tantrika lay asleep near the fire.  Adore paced patrol around the party's perimeter.  Rod watched the pale glow pinpricks pass in and out of veiw as the shambling mound of skeletal death-denial incarnate weave tween tree and a huge mound of blue tinted green that grinded noisily on the bone of a rather large creature.  <br>
<br>
Bloodclot's eyes penetrated into the boy's.  &quot;Gud.  Yer turn.  Watch well.&quot;  The eyes, sickening green like cabbage left under the sun, slid closed.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Hey, B.&quot;  Rodlac hesitated.  The eyes slit open slightly.  Grunt. &quot;You knew my father and all, and well...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You want to know about him?  Understood.  He die fore you born.  Natural to want.&quot;  Bloodclot shifted his bulk, his neck popping like the rending of flesh from a dragons spine twisted open with a dull awl weilded by a compolsive skitzophrenic.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Dis tell, old story.  Old like mother though not as pretty.&quot;   Bloodclot looked to Tantrika.  &quot;By lil ones standards least.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Meet Cal-Door in sands, we see soon dat.  Sand gi-ant stomp jelly.  Me still young and weak in shaman ways.  Me seek shelter on pillar in tear water.  Cal-Door der wit mudder.  Both hurt in bad way.  Eyes shifty, warey.&quot;  Bloodclot's stature suddenly changed.  His shoulders lifted, chest high, cabbage eyes to the skyline.  He voice, as he continued, boomed and sheltered, like a preacher offering last bastion.  <br>
<br>
Bloodclot approached the two slowly.  Many hummies not like trollies, fer no gud reason.  Hurt as dey were, there were a lil chance, fer Bloodclot knew ways of mending flesh an bone.  Skellie approach as green toes leave da tear water.  It wave rusty metal at Bloodclot.  He hold metal in hand, not making skellie jelly.  Male hummie stand, hand on pillar, strong wood in hands.  Inkie finger pretty red lights in air.  Bloodclot nervous.  <br>
<br>
Bloodclot seek shelter, no blood.  Hummie and inkie warey, agree.  Refuse mending.  Sit opposite side pillar.  Sleep light, nervous.  <br>
<br>
Footsteps splash, splash, splash, grind like troll teeth on gnome skull.  Eyes open, sandie on pillar.  Lil ones scared, panic.  Bloodclot panic same.  Look to water, croc eyes bubble surface all round.  Shark, but not.  <br>
<br>
Dey share shelter wit bloodclot, bloodclot owe dem.  Bloodclot chant shaman toughts.  Magi bolt hit gi-ant toe.  Gi-ant look annoyed, look to Bloodclot.  Fist high, aim fer bloodclot.  Skellie rush giant, bee sting shin wit toothpick.  Hummie an inkie dive to tear water.  <br>
<br>
Gi-ant make skellie jelly, blodclot soon next.  Hold stance, prepare chant.  Gi-ant grunt in pain, reach fer back of neck.  Look annoyed. It turn round.  Hummie stand on shore. He make finger gesture to gi-ant.  Gi-ant run to hummie, follow to dune, smack hard.  Hummie fall to ground, not move.  <br>
<br>
Bolt of magi flashin distance.  Gi-ant follow, kill face set.  <br>
Bloodclot come to inkie.  Say he sorry, too weak to do more.  Inkie shrug, say &quot;Do not worry, Caldor is quit fine, I expect.&quot;  Inkie slink to ground, hurt too much to take no longer.  <br>
<br>
Bloodclot walk to da Cal-door hummie.  Chant spell of mend.  Hummie twitch, red flow stills.  It stands, but weak.  Cal-door look at jelly ribs, wrap white cloth round dem.  Seem stronger.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you.&quot;  Cal-door spoke through mouth blood froth. &quot;Perhaps we three should move to safer grounds and heal a bit?&quot;<br>
<br>
Bloodclot walk toward swamp.  Hummie say dat not safe fer dem.  Collects inkie girl, move to Fee-port.  Bloodclot hesitate.  Cal-door say he know place, move safe.  Bloodclot nod, sencing gi-ant still anger to him and inkie. <br>
<br>
Dey come to Fee-port wall.  Inkie girl feel round wall.  Hand pass through.  She walk in wall, Cal-door follow, so Bloodclot follow.  <br>
<br>
Damp, torch lit, safe.  Da tee of dem slump to ground.  No watch dis night.  Too weak.  <br>
<br>
Story told, Bloodclot closed his cabbage eyes.  Rodlac waits a moment them realizes the troll means to sleep.  &quot;But what then?&quot;  Rod asked.  &quot;That can't be the whole story.  <br>
<br>
Bloodclot snored.  Rod sighed, knowing full well that he should let sleeping trolls lay.  He heard clanking nearby.  Adore, during its patrol, paused during the story.  It moved along its course just as Rodlac looked to it.  <br>
<br>
Rodlac stood and walked into the darkness.  He thought of the story as he relieved his aching bladder.  <br>
